@spec tm_tail_gating_spec  src=tests/specs/tm_tail_gating_spec.lua  loc=45  sha=c3b9b58  cases=1
@exercises midiManager (h.fm), dataStore (h.ds), trackerManager (h.tm)
@surface   fm:dump, ds:assign, tm:fromLogical
@harness   mk{seed.length, seed.notes}

# Intent
  Phase A of the dirt spine (design/dirty-channels.md § Scheme): the tail walk's clip/nudge
  is gated per dirty channel. An open note clips its raw tail to the next same-lane onset,
  realised under swing -- so a swing change must reseat that clip. Swing dirt is config, not
  carried by the mm reload payload; markSwingStale feeds the spine (A1), and the tail gate must
  honour it or the clipped tail wrongly keeps its old seat. This pins that on the tail path.

# Helpers
  @fn noteByPitch(notes, pitch)  @ 12-14

# Cases
  @case 'swing change reseats an open tail through the dirtyChans gate'  [harness]  @ 18-43

# Uses (outbound edges)
  @use call midiManager.dump  @ 32,39
  @use call dataStore.assign  @ 37
  @use call trackerManager.fromLogical  @ 40
